cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SE

This paper discusses the deanonymization of Bitcoin transactions and proposes a new anonymization technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network protocols and communication, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance and practical applications of the proposed technology, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves privacy and anonymity, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
